{
  "model": "unknown",
  "total_claims": 40,
  "claims": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "text": "The derivation assumes spherical symmetry: the metric depends only on the radial coordinate r and the angular coordinates \u03b8, \u03c6.",
      "type": "assumption",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The derivation assumes staticity: the metric is time-independent and has no off-diagonal terms mixing time and space.",
      "type": "assumption",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The derivation assumes vacuum: outside the mass, the energy-momentum tensor vanishes, T_{\u03bc\u03bd} = 0.",
      "type": "assumption",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The derivation assumes asymptotic flatness: as r \u2192 \u221e, the metric approaches the Minkowski metric.",
      "type": "assumption",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "The most general metric satisfying these conditions is ds\u00b2 = -A(r)c\u00b2dt\u00b2 + B(r)dr\u00b2 + r\u00b2d\u03b8\u00b2 + r\u00b2sin\u00b2\u03b8 d\u03c6\u00b2.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [
        1,
        2,
        3,
        4
      ],
      "notes": "This is the standard ansatz in Schwarzschild coordinates."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "In vacuum, the Einstein equations reduce to R_{\u03bc\u03bd} = 0.",
      "type": "invocation_of_known_result",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [
        3
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "text": "\u0393^t_{tr} = \u0393^t_{rt} = A'/(2A)",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "text": "\u0393^r_{tt} = c\u00b2A'/(2B)",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "text": "\u0393^r_{rr} = B'/(2B)",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "text": "\u0393^r_{\u03b8\u03b8} = -r/B",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "text": "\u0393^r_{\u03c6\u03c6} = -r sin\u00b2\u03b8 / B",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "text": "\u0393^\u03b8_{r\u03b8} = \u0393^\u03b8_{\u03b8r} = 1/r",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "text": "\u0393^\u03b8_{\u03c6\u03c6} = -sin\u03b8 cos\u03b8",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "text": "\u0393^\u03c6_{r\u03c6} = \u0393^\u03c6_{\u03c6r} = 1/r",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "text": "\u0393^\u03c6_{\u03b8\u03c6} = \u0393^\u03c6_{\u03c6\u03b8} = cot\u03b8",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "text": "R_{tt} = (c\u00b2/2B)A'' - c\u00b2(A')\u00b2/(4AB) - c\u00b2A'B'/(4B\u00b2) + c\u00b2A'/(rB)",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        7,
        8,
        9,
        10,
        11,
        12,
        13,
        14,
        15
      ],
      "notes": "Should be verified against standard references."
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "text": "R_{rr} = -A''/(2A) + (A')\u00b2/(4A\u00b2) + A'B'/(4AB) + B'/(rB)",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        7,
        8,
        9,
        10,
        11,
        12,
        13,
        14,
        15
      ],
      "notes": "Should be verified against standard references."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "text": "R_{\u03b8\u03b8} = 1 - 1/B + r/(2B)(B'/B - A'/A)",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        7,
        8,
        9,
        10,
        11,
        12,
        13,
        14,
        15
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "text": "R_{\u03c6\u03c6} = sin\u00b2\u03b8 R_{\u03b8\u03b8}",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        18
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "text": "From R_{tt}=0 and R_{rr}=0, after algebraic manipulation, we obtain A'/A + B'/B = 0.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        6,
        16,
        17
      ],
      "notes": "Intermediate algebra not shown explicitly."
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "text": "A'/A + B'/B = 0 implies (AB)' = 0.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        20
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "text": "AB = constant follows from (AB)' = 0.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        21
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "text": "Asymptotic flatness requires A \u2192 1 and B \u2192 1 as r \u2192 \u221e, so the constant AB = 1.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        4,
        22
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "text": "Therefore B = 1/A.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        23
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "text": "Substituting B = 1/A into R_{\u03b8\u03b8} = 0 gives 2(1/A - 1) + r(-2A'/A) = 0.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        18,
        24,
        6
      ],
      "notes": "Intermediate substitution step; factor of 2 should be checked."
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "text": "This simplifies to 1/A - 1 - rA'/A = 0.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        25
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "text": "Multiplying by A gives 1 - A - rA' = 0.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        26
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "text": "1 - A - rA' = 0 can be rewritten as (rA)' = 1.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        27
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "text": "Integrating (rA)' = 1 gives rA = r + C, so A = 1 + C/r.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        28
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "text": "In the weak-field limit, general relativity must reduce to Newtonian gravity.",
      "type": "assumption",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "text": "For a point mass M, the Newtonian potential is \u03a6 = -GM/r.",
      "type": "invocation_of_known_result",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "text": "The metric component g_{tt} is related to \u03a6 by g_{tt} \u2248 -(1 + 2\u03a6/c\u00b2)c\u00b2.",
      "type": "invocation_of_known_result",
      "provenance": "cited",
      "depends_on": [
        30
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "text": "Our solution gives g_{tt} = -Ac\u00b2 = -c\u00b2(1 + C/r) = -c\u00b2 - c\u00b2C/r.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5,
        29
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "text": "Comparing g_{tt} from the weak-field limit and our solution: -c\u00b2C/r = 2GM/r, so C = -2GM/c\u00b2.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        31,
        32,
        33
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "text": "A = 1 - 2GM/(c\u00b2r) and B = 1/(1 - 2GM/(c\u00b2r)).",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        24,
        29,
        34
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "text": "The Schwarzschild metric is ds\u00b2 = -(1 - 2GM/(c\u00b2r))c\u00b2dt\u00b2 + (1 - 2GM/(c\u00b2r))\u207b\u00b9dr\u00b2 + r\u00b2d\u03b8\u00b2 + r\u00b2sin\u00b2\u03b8 d\u03c6\u00b2.",
      "type": "numerical_result",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        5,
        35
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "text": "The metric exhibits a coordinate singularity where g_{rr} diverges and g_{tt} vanishes.",
      "type": "physical_interpretation",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        36
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "text": "Setting 1 - 2GM/(c\u00b2r) = 0 gives r_s = 2GM/c\u00b2.",
      "type": "derivation_step",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        37
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "text": "r_s = 2GM/c\u00b2 defines the Schwarzschild radius.",
      "type": "numerical_result",
      "provenance": "derived",
      "depends_on": [
        38
      ],
      "notes": ""
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "text": "The Schwarzschild radius is a coordinate singularity, not a physical one, as can be shown by transforming to other coordinates (e.g., Kruskal-Szekeres).",
      "type": "physical_interpretation",
      "provenance": "asserted",
      "depends_on": [
        39
      ],
      "notes": ""
    }
  ]
}